## iCinema – Frontend Architecture & UI Design Document (React + Bootstrap)

---

# 1. Frontend Overview

This document defines the **frontend architecture, UI layout, and implementation plan** for the iCinema project using:

- React + TypeScript (TSX)
- Bootstrap & React-Bootstrap
- Axios for API calls
- React Router DOM for routing

No authentication, no Redux/Zustand, no custom CSS files, and no extra libraries are used.

---

# 2. Frontend Folder Structure (BEGINNER LEVEL)

```
src/
  components/
    Navbar.tsx
    MovieCard.tsx
    MovieCarousel.tsx
    MovieFilterBar.tsx
    SeatGrid.tsx
    BookingSummary.tsx
    PaymentForm.tsx

  models/
    Movie.ts
    Show.ts
    Seat.ts
    BookingSummary.ts
    Payment.ts

  pages/
    HomePage.tsx
    MoviesPage.tsx
    MovieDetailsPage.tsx
    ShowSelectionPage.tsx
    SeatSelectionPage.tsx
    BookingSummaryPage.tsx
    PaymentPage.tsx
    TicketPage.tsx

  App.tsx
  main.tsx
```

---

# 3. UI Design Philosophy

## 3.1 Design References

- **Booking Flow, Show Selection, Seat Matrix** → Inspired by BookMyShow (industry standard UX)
- **Home Page & Movies Page** → Unique Netflix/Amazon-style grid layout

## 3.2 Styling Rules

- Only Bootstrap classes (`container`, `row`, `col`, `card`, `carousel`, etc.)
- No CSS files
- No Tailwind, Material UI, or external UI frameworks

---

# 4. Page-Level UI Design

## 4.1 Home Page (/)

### Unique UI Design

- Dark theme hero carousel (Netflix-style)
- Horizontal trending movies row
- Info feature cards

### Bootstrap Layout

```
<Container fluid>
  <Navbar />
  <Carousel />
  <Container>
    <Row><h3>Trending Movies</h3></Row>
    <Row className="d-flex flex-row flex-nowrap overflow-auto"><MovieCard /></Row>
    <Row className="mt-4">
      <Col md={4}><Card>Easy Booking</Card></Col>
      <Col md={4}><Card>Secure Payment</Card></Col>
      <Col md={4}><Card>Real-time Seats</Card></Col>
    </Row>
    <Row className="mt-4"><h3>Currently Playing</h3></Row>
    <Row><Col md={3}><MovieCard /></Col></Row>
  </Container>
</Container>
```

---

## 4.2 Movies Page (/movies)

### Unique Design (NOT BookMyShow clone)

- Left filter sidebar
- Right movie grid explorer

### Layout

```
<Row>
  <Col md={3}><Accordion>Filters</Accordion></Col>
  <Col md={9}>
    <Form.Control placeholder="Search Movies" />
    <Row className="mt-3"><Col md={3}><MovieCard /></Col></Row>
  </Col>
</Row>
```

Features:

- Pagination (20 movies per page)
- Filters: Genre, Language, Rating
- Search using backend API

---

## 4.3 Movie Details Page (/movies/:id)

Displays:

- Poster, Name, Genre, Language, Rating, Release Date, Description
- Rating Input Box (1–5 stars)
- Book My Show Button

---

## 4.4 Show Selection Page (/shows/:movieId)

- List of theatres and show times
- Clicking show → seat count page

---

## 4.5 Seat Count & Pricing Page

- Input number of seats
- Call pricing API
- Show total estimated cost

---

## 4.6 Seat Selection Page (/seats/:showId)

### BookMyShow-Style UX

- Seat grid (A1, A2, B1...)
- Colors:
  - Green = Available
  - Red = Booked
  - Yellow = Selected

### Layout

```
<Row>
  <Col md={9}><SeatGrid /></Col>
  <Col md={3}><BookingSummary /></Col>
</Row>
```

---

## 4.7 Booking Summary Page

- Seat price
- Convenience fee
- GST
- Total amount
- Pay Now button

---

## 4.8 Payment Page

### Mock Payment UI

- Credit / Debit card selection
- Card Number, Expiry, CVV fields
- Discounts:
  - Credit Card → 10%
  - Debit Card → 5%

---

## 4.9 Ticket Confirmation Page

Displays final ticket details:

- Movie Name
- Seats
- Theatre
- Show Time
- Amount Paid

---

# 5. API Integration Pattern (BEGINNER STYLE)

### Example Axios Call

```
useEffect(() => {
  axios.get("http://localhost:8080/movies/allMovies")
    .then(res => setMovies(res.data));
}, []);
```

### Example POST Payment

```
const handlePay = () => {
  axios.post("http://localhost:8080/api/payment/pay", paymentData)
    .then(res => setResult(res.data));
};
```

---

# 6. Beginner React State Rules

- Use useState for movies, seats, selectedSeats, totalPrice
- Pass props between components
- No Redux/Zustand/Context global state

---

# 7. Notes for Junior Developer

- Do not add CSS files
- Do not add service folders
- Do not add DTO folders in frontend
- Write axios directly in components
- Keep components simple and readable

---

